# # Purpose & Function
#
# Purpose: Guide developers to write clear, informative commit messages
#
# Core Design: Structured template following Bereshit keying conventions
#
# Key Features:
#
#   - Subject line with domain keying ([DOMAIN/path] TYPE: Description)
#   - Structured body sections (What, Why, Impact, References)
#   - Consistent format across all contributors
#   - Searchable commit history
#
# Philosophy: Commit messages tell the story of the codebase - make them count
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# INTERFACE (Expected)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# # Dependencies
#
# What This Needs:
#
#   - Git: Version control system that uses .gitmessage
#   - Git Config: commit.template set to point to this file
#
# What Uses This:
#
#   - git commit (opens editor with this template pre-filled)
#   - Developers writing commits
#   - CI/CD systems reading commit messages
#
# Integration Points:
#
#   - Global: git config --global commit.template ~/.gitmessage
#   - Local: git config commit.template .gitmessage
#
# # Usage & Integration
#
# Git Configuration:
#
#   # Set globally (all repos)
#   git config --global commit.template ~/.gitmessage
#
#   # Set per-repo
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
#
# When Triggered:
#   - Running `git commit` (without -m flag)
#   - Editor opens with template pre-filled
#   - Developer fills in sections, removes unused ones
